    "Body": " Customer Success Associate Apto Payments - San Francisco, CA Quick Apply Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $51,000 - $69,000 a year11 days ago Benefits Flexible Schedule Qualifications Account Management Financial Services Full Job Description About us: Apto Payments is a leading-edge card issuance platform. We help companies issue new kinds of cards in new ways. We do it with fewer constraints and more creativity, for a better cardholder experience. Founded in 2014 as Shift Payments, the company worked with Coinbase to launch the first Bitcoin debit card. Today, as Apto, we have broadened our mission, finding new ways to connect people to their assets by helping \u2013 crypto and non-crypto related \u2013 companies successfully launch innovative, customer-centric card programs to market. Apto is a Series A company, headquartered in San Francisco. We are focused on growing our business in a responsible way by building transformative, best-in-class products while managing our risk exposure. We're excited about empowering developers' and customers' abilities to launch the most innovative card programs, in the most efficient way possible. Role: We are seeking an experienced customer success associate to serve as the point of contact for client developers as they go through our Developer Portal. Our customer\u2019s needs are constantly changing, and we would like this individual to take ownership of pre- and post-launch technical questions, fielding requests, and maintaining client relationships. We want this person to have a significant presence in the company to help drive the company\u2019s success. This means developing strong relationships across the company; up, down and across. We want fun, creative colleagues who are passionate about the problems they\u2019re solving and we want you to share those messages with everyone. Job requirements: Support developers through the onboarding process Support our current customers, post-launch, by maintaining client relationships, fielding requests, and holding meetings. Assist Customer Success Manager in implementations, onboarding new developers/bespoke programs, and administrative tasks. Assist the team in creating efficient processes. Understand the technical side of the Apto platform and be able to speak to current and potential customers\u2019 product and engineering teams. Have relevant knowledge in financial services, preferably payments, and specifically in transaction processing. Communicate with clarity and charisma. Explain technical concepts in a digestible manner. Be excited about to customer-facing responsibilities Explain technical solutions to a diverse audience using appropriate language. Skills/Qualities: Prior experience in Account Management or other customer-facing role . Familiarity in payments industry is a plus. Maintain a level of curiosity in our product and how to improve it. You are not afraid to tackle tasks as they arise. You\u2019ve previously held a role that required managing multiple tasks. You can cross communicate between teams effectively. You can work well both individually and as part of a team. Benefits: Competitive salary and equity Fully paid healthcare for you and dependants Great team of driven people with different skill sets Flexible hours and work from home days (fully remote during COVID-19) Opportunity to build solutions for millions of people around the world Powered by JazzHR aAfu4nFqjy ", 
